<p>Since October 1st, 2017, I am Ph.D. candidate at <a href="http://www.inria.fr">Inria</a> in the <a href="https://team.inria.fr/panama/">PANAMA team</a> of the <a href="https://www.inria.fr/centre/rennes">Inria Rennes</a>.</p>

<p>I am working under the supervision of <a href="https://members.loria.fr/ADeleforge/">Antoine Deleforge</a> and <a href="https://team.inria.fr/panama/author/nbertin/">Nancy Bertin</a> on the thesis: <em>Hunting Echoes for Auditory Scene Analysis</em>.</p>

<p>My research interest are:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Machine Learning:
    <ul>
      <li>Regression and classification</li>
      <li>Deep learning</li>
      <li>Bayesian and Latent variable models</li>
      <li>Non-negative matrix factorization</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Auditory Scene Analysis:
    <ul>
      <li>Room Impulse Response and Acoustic Channel Estimation and Simulators</li>
      <li><em>Echo-aware</em> speech enhancements</li>
      <li>Room geometry reconstruction</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Audio signal processing and inverse problems
    <ul>
      <li>Sound source localization and separation</li>
      <li>De-reverberation</li>
      <li>Convolutive and probabilistic mixing models</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

